Three boys were involved in an altercation on school grounds, leaving two of them wounded. CAPE TOWN - Lentegeur police detectives are investigating a case of assault after two pupils were stabbed at Lentegeur High School on Monday morning. Three boys were involved in an altercation on the school grounds, leaving two of them wounded. Both learners and teachers are traumatised and have been receiving counselling at the school. The police's Frederick van Wyk said: “Two of the learners were admitted to hospital with injuries around their arms and legs. A third learner was taken to hospital and allegedly ran away. The motive for this incident is currently unknown and investigations continue.” (Edited by Mihlali Ntsabo)